17/03/2006
ATHENS, Greece -- A meeting between Greek Foreign Minister Dora Bakoyannis and US Secretary of State Condoleezza Rice is planned for next week, during Bakoyannis' official visit to Washington. 
According to a statement issued on Thursday (16 March), talks would cover a broad range of issues.
In other news Thursday, the Turkish media reported that Foreign Minister Abdullah Gul would probably meet with Rice, as well as with UN Secretary General Kofi Annan, during a visit to the United States later this month. 
Gul will be attending the annual gathering of the American-Turkish Council. 
(Kathimerini, Focus - 17/03/06; ANA - 16/03/06)
